# 010 - MarketLab Profile & Market Images Integration

Enhance the MarketLab auth-aware UI and Supabase Storage integration.

Context:
The authentication flow already exists. Follow AGENTS.md and existing Supabase client/server patterns. Keep the UI consistent with the current clean dashboard design and light/dark theme support.

The final goal is:
1. User profile avatars in the navbar.
2. An Edit Account view for profile updates.
3. Supabase Storage buckets for user avatars and market images.
4. Market images displayed cleanly in /markets and /markets/[id].
5. No broken image placeholders, fallback text, or unwanted layout shifts.

Navbar & Avatar Dropdown

Update the signed-in navbar state:
- Replace the standalone Sign Out button with a clickable user avatar.
- Fetch the avatar reference from the current user's profile.
- If the user has an uploaded avatar, show it.
- If the user has no avatar, show initials fallback.
- Clicking the avatar opens an accessible dropdown.
- Dropdown options:
  - Edit Account
  - Sign Out
- Dropdown must close when clicking outside and work with keyboard navigation.
- Styling must match the app in light and dark modes.

Edit Account View

Create an /account route:
- Require authentication.
- Load current profile data.
- Add a clear navigation link above the form to return to the main markets/dashboard view.
  - The link should be visually consistent with the app.
  - Suggested label: “Back to Markets” or “Back to Dashboard”.
- Show editable first name and last name fields.
- Show email as visible but strictly disabled/read-only.
- Include profile picture upload.
- Upload avatar files to Supabase Storage bucket avatars.
- Store avatar path/reference in profiles.avatar_path.
- Validate avatar uploads:
  - Image files only.
  - Max size around 5 MB.
- When the user selects an avatar file, immediately preview the selected image in the Edit Account view.
  - The preview should update instantly before saving.
  - The preview should not upload or replace the existing Supabase avatar yet.
  - The existing avatar in Supabase should only be replaced after the user clicks the Save button.
  - If the user selects a different file before saving, update the preview to the newest selected file.
  - If no new image is selected, keep showing the current avatar or initials fallback.
  - Do not show broken image icons or fallback text if the preview fails.
- After saving, refresh/revalidate so the navbar avatar updates without a full browser reload.
- Do not expose service role or privileged keys to the browser.

Supabase Storage & Database

Create migrations for:
- profiles.avatar_path
- markets.image_path
- Storage bucket avatars
- Storage bucket market_images

Profile/avatar RLS:
- Users can read their own profile.
- Users can update only their own profile row.
- Profile update policy must use both USING and WITH CHECK.
- Anyone may view avatars.
- Authenticated users can upload/update/delete only avatar files in their own folder:
  {user_id}/avatar.{extension}

Market images:
- Bucket name: market_images
- Public-readable.
- No UI for uploading market images.
- Images are uploaded manually in Supabase Storage.
- The full public Storage URL is manually stored in markets.image_path.
- Also optionally support object-path fallback if useful, but the primary workflow is storing the full public URL.

Market Image URL Logic

Implement a helper like resolveMarketImageUrl():
- If image_path is null, empty, or whitespace, return null.
- If image_path starts with http:// or https://, use it directly.
- If it is only an object path, optionally build:
  {SUPABASE_URL}/storage/v1/object/public/market_images/{image_path}

Market Image Component Behavior

Create a reusable MarketImage component:
- Client component.
- Receives imageUrl.
- If no URL, render nothing.
- If the image fails to load, render nothing.
- Do not show broken image icons.
- Do not show alt fallback text.
- Use alt="" and aria-hidden.
- Show the image immediately when a valid URL exists.
- Use onError to hide/remove it only if it fails.
- Use a key={imageUrl ?? market.id} when rendering per market so cached/navigation changes do not prevent image display.

Market Cards (/markets)

Display the market image inside each card if the market has one.

Final visual requirements:
- Image should appear as a small thumbnail on the top-right side.
- It should sit below the Open status badge.
- Suggested size: 56px × 56px (size-14).
- Use object-cover, rounded corners, and subtle border/ring.
- Cards with images must not become visually taller than cards without images.
- Cards without images must not display placeholders or fallback text.
- Reserve consistent top-right space for the image area so title/content alignment stays clean.
- The card grid should use equal-height cards per row.
- The footer (Closes... and View) should stay aligned at the bottom.
- The description should use natural height and should not create a large gap below it.
- Avoid forcing min-height on the description itself.
- If extra flexible space is needed to keep the footer aligned, place it between description and footer, not inside the description.

Recommended card structure:
- Left top area:
  - Yes / No market
  - title
- Right top area:
  - status badge
  - small market image thumbnail if available
- Middle:
  - description
- Bottom:
  - divider
  - close date
  - View button

Selected Market View (/markets/[id])

Also show the market image in the selected market detail view.

Final visual requirements:
- Show the image in the top-right area of the market detail info panel.
- It should appear below the status badge.
- Suggested size: 80px × 80px (size-20).
- Use object-cover, rounded corners, and subtle border/ring.
- If the market has no image or the image fails, show nothing extra.
- Keep title and market metadata aligned cleanly on the left.
- Do not show a large hero image unless explicitly requested.

Testing / Verification

If tests exist, add/update focused tests for:
- Avatar fallback initials.
- Avatar URL handling.
- Header signed-in avatar dropdown.
- Edit Account form with disabled email field.
- Edit Account back navigation link.
- Avatar upload immediate local preview behavior.
- Avatar preview does not upload or replace Supabase storage until Save is clicked.
- Avatar upload validation and storage upload path.
- resolveMarketImageUrl() behavior:
  - null/empty returns null
  - full public URL is used directly
  - optional object path fallback works
- Market cards render MarketImage.
- Market detail view renders MarketImage.
- MarketImage uses alt="", handles onError, and does not rely on hidden loading state that can break cached images.
- Market card layout reserves image space and keeps equal-height cards.

